#. type: Title ==
#: composingemail.adoc:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "Customizing Your Options for Composing Messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:64
msgid ""
"From your preferences you can select to create simple plain text messages or "
"create messages with HTML styling, and you can set up signatures and "
"personas that can be applied to messages you send."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:69
msgid ""
"In addition to the options for composing messages, other options you can set "
"up include return receipt requests, whether to compose messages in a new "
"window and to require that your messages are spell checked before they are "
"sent."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:71 replyandforwardmessages.adoc:10
#: replyandforwardmessages.adoc:71
msgid "Go to the *Preferences>Mail* page, *Composing Messages* section."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:73
msgid "Select how you want your messages to be sent, *As HTML* or *As Text*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:76
msgid ""
"If you select *As HTML*, in the drop down menus, select the *Font* style, "
"*Size*, and *Color*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: composingemail.adoc:79
msgid ""
"In *Settings*, select the options for how you want to manage composing "
"messages."
msgstr ""

